UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X97000111
KW  - Trading costs
KW  - Quote rounding
KW  - Nasdaq market
AB  - This paper investigates relations between trade execution costs and price-rounding practices for NYSE- and Nasdaq-listed firms. Execution costs on each exchange vary positively with the proportion of transaction prices and quotations rounded to eveneights of a dollar, both cross-sectionally and intertemporally. After allowing for variation in market-making costs attributable to the private information content of trades, there is a strong positive relation between execution costs and price-rounding frequencies for Nasdaq issues but not for NYSE issues. These findings are consistent with the assertion that price-rounding conventions effectively increase trade execution costs on Nasdaq.
